AN ACT relating to real property; enacting the Uniform Easement
Relocation Act; enacting the Uniform Mortgage
Modification Act; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Sections 2-32 of this bill enact the Uniform Easement Relocation Act
2 promulgated by the Uniform Law Commission in 2020. Sections 34-50 of this bill
3 enact the Uniform Mortgage Modification Act promulgated by the Uniform Law
4 Commission in 2024.
5 Generally, the Uniform Easement Relocation Act allows the owner of real
6 property burdened by certain types of easements to seek judicial approval to
7 relocate an easement if the relocation does not materially impair the utility of the
8 easement to the easement holder or the physical condition, use or value of the
9 benefitted property. Sections 4-21 define certain terms for the purposes of the Act.
10 Section 22 prohibits relocation under the Act of an easement: (1) where the holder
11 is a publicly regulated or publicly owned utility or a public entity; (2) which has
12 been set aside for certain conservation purposes; (3) which is associated with a
13 public road; (4) which is a negative easement that imposes a duty not to engage in a
14 specified use of the property; (5) if the proposed location encroaches on certain
15 land or interferes with the use or enjoyment or certain other easements; or (6)
16 which is created by a declaration of a common-interest community.
17 Section 24: (1) requires a property owner who wishes to relocate an easement
18 under the Act to file a civil action and serve a summons and complaint on the
19 easement holder and certain other interested persons; and (2) sets forth the required
20 contents of such a complaint. Sections 23 and 25 set forth: (1) the factors a court
21 must consider before approving the relocation of an easement under the Act; and
22 (2) the required contents of a court order approving such a relocation. If the court
23 approves the relocation of an easement, section 27 requires all parties to the civil
24 action to act in good faith to facilitate relocation. Section 26 requires the property
-
